+{"title":"fix: alpha.13 (2/n) — salvage valid inline comments on a rejected review (#57)","body":"## Salvage valid inline comments when a batched review is rejected (#57)\n\nalpha.13 round, part 2. **Do not release on merge** — more PRs land before the single alpha.13 release.\n\nGitHub's `POST /pulls/:pr/reviews` is **atomic**: one comment on a position it won't accept rejects the *entire* review, so a single bad finding lost every inline comment **and** turned the comment job red (observed on PR #55's first review).\n\n### Fix — degrade, don't drop everything\n\n`postInlineReview` now, on rejection:\n1. posts the review **body-only** (so the review event + findings-JSON marker survive), then\n2. re-posts each comment **individually** via `/pulls/:pr/comments` — keeping the ones GitHub accepts and collecting the finding behind each one it rejects.\n\nIt returns `inlinePosted` (how many actually anchored) and `unposted` (the rejected findings). `post()` then **surfaces exactly the rejected findings in the sticky** — appended to the real out-of-diff strays, the section retitled **Findings** with a note (*\"N finding(s) below couldn't be posted as inline comments\"*) — so no finding is lost to human view, while the disposition reports only the count that truly anchored (issue #21: never a false \"posted N\").\n\nThe happy path is unchanged — a single atomic review POST, no extra calls. `buildInlineComments` now also returns `inDiff` (the finding behind each comment, 1:1) so a rejected comment maps back to its finding.\n\n### Validation\n\n- New `post` test: two in-diff findings, batched POST rejected, one comment accepted + one rejected → the review posts body-only, both comments retried individually, the sticky reports **1 posted inline** + surfaces only the **rejected** finding (the anchored one stays out of the sticky).\n- Full `camas ci` green (prettier, eslint, tsc, tests, actionlint, build).\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> **LLM Disclosure**\n>\n> This PR was authored by claude-opus-4-8 on behalf of @JPHutchins, who asked to fix the inline-posting failure as part of the alpha.13 series and specifically flagged that it should NOT be all-or-nothing — the valid comments should post and only the rejected ones fall back to the sticky.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n"}
